Anne J. BRADY, Appellant, v. Joseph A. CANTREL, Mildred Games, Appellees. No. 9988. United States Court of Appeals District of Columbia Circuit. Argued Nov. 7,1949. Decided Dec. 12, 1949. Mr. William B. O’Connell, Washington, D. G, with whom Mr. William A. Gallagher, Washington, D. G, was on the brief, for appellant. Mr. William T. Hannan, Washington, D. G, for appellee Cantrel. No appearance for appellee Games.

Before EDGERTON, McALLISTER, sitting by designation, and BAZELON, Circuit Judges.

*39PER CURIAM.

This suit involves the validity of various claims against the estate of J. Frank Brady, deceased. Some of the questions involved are res judicata. Brady v. Games, 76 U.S.App.D.C. 47, 128 F.2d 754. We find no prejudicial error in regard to the others. The judgment of the District Court is therefore affirmed.
